o hockey’s historically white dominated narratives and representations by returning hockey culture to its multicultural roots. It encourages alternative and multiple narratives about hockey and cultural citizenship by asking which citizens are able to contribute to the webs of meaning that form the nation’s cultural fabric.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHockeyxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aNational characteristics, Canadian. 0aSouth AsiansxCultural assimilationzCanada. 0aSouth AsianszCanadaxSocial conditions. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / General.2bisacsh  aCourtney Szto, assistant professor, Kinesiology, Health Studies, Queen’s University, Kingston, Ontario, Social Sciences, Humanities Research Council, Canada, Women, funded researcher, intersectional justice, Relationship, Physical Cultures, social constructs, Hockey Night, multiculturalism, hockey players, parents, coaches, British Columbia, Sociology, Sports, Recreation, Asian American Studies, Race, Ethnic Studies, Asian Studies, cultural citizenship.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197880797640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978807976423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978807976/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK